data.chText: 我丢了护照时觉得自己像个大傻瓜。
data.enText: When I lost my passport, I felt such an idiot.

data.chText: 不是那个开关，你这个蠢货！

data.enText: a person with very low intelligence who cannot think or behave normally

simple_means.memory_skill: idi〔o〕个人，特殊 + ot …人 → 特殊的个人 → 白痴

value.def: If you call someone an idiot, you are showing that you think they are very stupid or have done something very stupid.

example.ex: I knew I'd been an idiot to stay there...
example.tran: 我知道我呆在这里很蠢。

example.ex: ...a bunch of idiot journalists waiting to ask me stupid questions.
example.tran: 一帮白痴似的记者等着问我愚蠢的问题

value.def: In the past, people who had something wrong with their brains that made them seem less intelligent, or different from other people, were sometimes called idiots .

trans: 弱能特才，低能特才(有严重的学习障碍，但在艺术、音乐或记忆等方面有超常能力)

partsOfSpeech.dec: com 共同 + patri 父亲 + ot …人 → 同胞
idi〔o〕个人，特殊 + ot …人 → 特殊的个人 → 白痴
patri 父亲 + ot …人 → 爱国者
zeal 热情 + ot …人 → 热心者
